content.data: Hello, hello, hello, is there anybody in there, can you nod if you can hear me? Is there anyone at home?
All in all we're just a-nother brick in the wall.
Ticking away, the moments that make up a dog day.
Relax, relax, relax, I need some information. Just the basic facts, can you tell me where it hurts?
You can check out anytime you like, but you may never leave.
We're just two lost souls living in a fish bowl, year after year. Running over the same old ground. What have we found? The same old fears. Wish you were here.
There is no pain, you are receding. The distant shipsmoke on the horizon. You are only coming through in waves. Your lips move, but I can't hear what they're saying.
